   To Durakken: it's not a theory. it's fact. Video games that name characters too similarily have done it badly. So has Tolkien, in parts. Admittedly when you get to the sort of universe he created you're bound to run into difficulties, and many have done it far far worse. Take, for example, Robert Jordan novels. It happens all the time. How many twelve year olds knew how to pronounce &quot;Hermione&quot; when they first saw it? Bad naming. Rowling forgot who her audience was, or at least she pushed them aside for some reason of her own.<br>
